  "text": "The small size of the stochastic message brings two benefits. Firstly, it reduces the hardware complexity of the non-binary decoders both in the number of interconnection wires and in the processing units themselves [CITATION_1] . Secondly, shorter messages improve the average throughput when the received vector is close to a codeword and few cycles are enough for convergence. With alternative approaches, even if one iteration is required, larger messages have to be passed between the nodes resulting in reduced throughput.",
